## Goal 
- Understand how attackers discover hidden parts of a website.

-> Before exploiting anything we must know what pages exist on this website,Because many sensitive pages are not linked publicly.
- Example: we visit a website (http://target-site.com) and we see (Home | About | Contact) but the server also contain 
- /admin
- /login
- /uploads
- /dev
- /backup,
and these are not linked anywhere, attackers discover them through enumeration.

=> tool used for this is:
- A common tool used is Gobuster.
- Gobuster performs directory brute forcing.
- Meaning it tries many possible page names like:
-> /admin
-> /login
-> /config
-> /backup
until it finds pages that exist.

=> Example command: (gobuster dir -u http://target-site.com -w wordlist.txt), this checks thousands of possible directories.

# Why Hidden Pages Matter?
- Hidden directories often contain:
-> admin panels
-> development environments
-> backups
-> file uploads
-> configuration files

=> Example: (/admin), If this page exists, attackers might try:
-> default credentials
-> login bypass
-> brute force
